<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-195-608  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 195 608.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  Feb 26 1990 v36 n1798 p30(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Vendors intensify offshore marketing: as DOD cuts funding. (USDepartment of Defense)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robertson, Jack.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Defense contractors worried about budget reductions by the DOD areincreasing foreign marketing efforts.andP;  Codar Technologies willsell DEC MicroVAX 2 and 3 computers to Italy, Belgium and Denmark.andO;Litton Data Systems is attempting to supply the Swedish Army withan artillery fire control system based on its new tacticalcomputer.andP;  As others try to expand their markets, ElectrospaceSystems Inc, Ford Aerospace and Ford Motor Co's BDM subsidiary areattempting to convince domestic military customers that they aregoing concerns despite being up for sale.andP;  Despite severe cutbacksin military spending, analysts agree that secure militarycommunications systems will remain in demand.andP;  Upgrades andoff-the-shelf systems will be more popular than custom systems ornew developments.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Defense ContractsMilitaryMarketing StrategyInternational TradeComputer industry.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>